# https://orgmode.org/manual/Markup.html
# For using babel multi languages you have add them above and to wrap them around
# e.g. John 1:1 \selectlanguage{greek} Εν αρχῃ ην ο λογος, και ο λογος ην προς τον θεον, και θεος ην ο λογος.
# Then, \selectlanguage{english} John 2:1 (etc.). 
# see also: https://github.com/jkitchin/jmax/blob/master/examples/technical-documents-in-org.org
# see also: https://orgmode.org/manual/Export-settings.html#DOCF126
# you can use "#+ BEGiN_VERSE #+ END_VERSE" to format lines in a literal way
# or "#+ BEGIN_SRC raw #+ END_SRC" to format lines in a literal way - or:
# M-x org-insert-structure-template RET TAB. Then write the template you want, e.g. (python sh emacs-lisp etc.)
# use #+DATE: \today for adding a current date 
# use #+REVEAL: split for breaking the slides - if they are too big
# for inserting exporting options, you can use "M-x yas-insert-snippet"
# then you can use wps to open ".docx" and export the file to ".pdf"
# you can use "\" to break lines inside a paragraph
# for translating phrase/words, use "translate" yas-snippet after enclosing them into the code and call:
# M-x org-babel-execute-src-block-maybe (C-c C-c)
# you can use "\justify" and other key alightment words to format paragraphs 
# for organising footnotes, do: "Ctrl-x m RET org-footnote-normalize"
# for hyphenation you can write words into its curl brackets "{}"
# for inserting images you can use: file:path/to/image
# for playing songs inside org files you can use: "M-x mplayer-find-file" or dired-jump and then play it
